class="sr-only">ChatGPT said:</h6><div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:--spacing(4)] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(6)] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(16)] px-(--thread-content-margin)"><div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn" tabindex="-1"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col grow"><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="62b1ccea-fee1-46ca-a1f0-a746c87d4636" dir="auto" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="78">Got it Merin! 😊<br data-start="16" data-end="19">
I can clearly see the paper you uploaded in the screenshot.</p>
<h3 data-start="80" data-end="118">✅ <strong data-start="86" data-end="116">This is NOT an IEEE paper.</strong></h3>
<p data-start="119" data-end="299">It is a <strong data-start="127" data-end="158">college-level seminar paper</strong> prepared by students from <em data-start="185" data-end="226">Santhigiri College of Computer Sciences</em>.<br data-start="227" data-end="230">
So it is <strong data-start="239" data-end="246">not</strong> a journal paper, not IEEE, not Springer, not Scopus.</p>
<h3 data-start="301" data-end="377">📌 Should you use this paper for your 6th semester seminar comparison?</h3>
<p data-start="378" data-end="531"><strong data-start="378" data-end="384">No</strong>, because your two selected papers are:<br data-start="423" data-end="426">
✔ Paper 1 – AI &amp; Cybersecurity (literature review)<br data-start="476" data-end="479">
✔ Paper 2 – Recent Advances of AI in Cybersecurity</p>
<p data-start="533" data-end="612">This blockchain paper is completely <strong data-start="569" data-end="589">different domain</strong>, so you don’t need it.</p>
<h3 data-start="614" data-end="728">If you uploaded it just to show a reference format → I can prepare your seminar report in the <strong data-start="712" data-end="727">same format</strong>.</h3>
<p data-start="730" data-end="838">If you want me to follow this formatting style for your rough report (two-column IEEE-like format), tell me:</p>
<p data-start="840" data-end="890">💬 <strong data-start="843" data-end="890">“Prepare my report exactly in this format.”</strong></p>
