</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="1135" data-end="1168"><strong data-start="1139" data-end="1166">4. Comparative Analysis</strong></h3>
<ul data-start="1169" data-end="1597">
<li data-start="1169" data-end="1222">
<p data-start="1171" data-end="1222"><strong data-start="1171" data-end="1190">Algorithms used</strong>: similarities and differences</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1223" data-end="1298">
<p data-start="1225" data-end="1298"><strong data-start="1225" data-end="1250">Input parameters/data</strong>: what datasets or information each paper uses</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1299" data-end="1376">
<p data-start="1301" data-end="1376"><strong data-start="1301" data-end="1322">Application areas</strong>: domains like healthcare, finance, network security</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1377" data-end="1430">
<p data-start="1379" data-end="1430"><strong data-start="1379" data-end="1392">Strengths</strong>: unique contributions of each paper</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1431" data-end="1533">
<p data-start="1433" data-end="1533"><strong data-start="1433" data-end="1459">Limitations/Challenges</strong>: issues like false positives, ethical concerns, implementation barriers</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1534" data-end="1597">
<p data-start="1536" data-end="1597">Optional: <strong data-start="1546" data-end="1565">Table or figure</strong> showing side-by-side comparison</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="1599" data-end="1622"><strong data-start="1603" data-end="1620">5. Conclusion</strong></h3>
<ul data-start="1623" data-end="1743">
<li data-start="1623" data-end="1659">
<p data-start="1625" data-end="1659">Key findings from the comparison</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1660" data-end="1698">
<p data-start="1662" data-end="1698">Role of AI in modern cybersecurity</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1699" data-end="1743">
<p data-start="1701" data-end="1743">Future directions or improvements needed</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="1745" data-end="1765"><strong data-start="1749" data-end="1763">References</strong></h3>
<ul data-start="1766" data-end="1815">
<li data-start="1766" data-end="1815">
<p data-start="1768" data-end="1815">Properly formatted references for both papers</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1817" data-end="1820">
<p data-start="1822" data-end="1917">If you want, I can <strong data-start="1841" data-end="1883">now create the full Word seminar paper</strong> with this structure, including:</p>
