t break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-mini"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="130">Sure Merin! For your seminar report, here’s a clean way to divide it into <strong data-start="74" data-end="99">five main subheadings</strong> that cover everything clearly:</p>
<hr data-start="132" data-end="135">
<h2 data-start="137" data-end="165"><strong data-start="140" data-end="165">Suggested Subheadings</strong></h2>
<ol data-start="167" data-end="932">
<li data-start="167" data-end="307">
<p data-start="170" data-end="188"><strong data-start="170" data-end="186">Introduction</strong></p>
<ul data-start="192" data-end="307">
<li data-start="192" data-end="229">
<p data-start="194" data-end="229">Importance of AI in cybersecurity</p>
</li>
<li data-start="233" data-end="272">
<p data-start="235" data-end="272">Objectives of the comparative study</p>
</li>
<li data-start="276" data-end="307">
<p data-start="278" data-end="307">Overview of selected papers</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="309" data-end="493">
<p data-start="312" data-end="335"><strong data-start="312" data-end="333">Literature Survey</strong></p>
<ul data-start="339" data-end="493">
<li data-start="339" data-end="386">
<p data-start="341" data-end="386">Summary of Paper 1 (impact and limitations)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="390" data-end="451">
<p data-start="392" data-end="451">Summary of Paper 2 (recent advancements and applications)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="455" data-end="493">
<p data-start="457" data-end="493">Key findings from previous studies</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="495" data-end="710">
<p data-start="498" data-end="524"><strong data-start="498" data-end="522">Comparative Analysis</strong></p>
<ul data-start="528" data-end="710">
<li data-start="528" data-end="547">
<p data-start="530" data-end="547">Algorithms used</p>
</li>
<li data-start="551" data-end="582">
<p data-start="553" data-end="582">Input parameters / datasets</p>
</li>
<li data-start="586" data-end="617">
<p data-start="588" data-end="617">Application areas / domains</p>
</li>
<li data-start="621" data-end="650">
<p data-start="623" data-end="650">Strengths and limitations</p>
</li>
<li data-start="654" data-end="710">
<p data-start="656" data-end="710">Optional table or figure for side-by-side comparison</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="712" data-end="852">
<p data-start="715" data-end="731"><strong data-start="715" data-end="729">Conclusion</strong></p>
<ul data-start="735" data-end="852">
<li data-start="735" data-end="769">
<p data-start="737" data-end="769">Key outcomes of the comparison</p>
</li>
<li data-start="773" data-end="811">
<p data-start="775" data-end="811">Role of AI in modern cybersecurity</p>
</li>
<li data-start="815" data-end="852">
<p data-start="817" data-end="852">Future directions or improvements</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="854" data-end="932">
<p data-start="857" data-end="873"><strong data-start="857" data-end="871">References</strong></p>
<ul data-start="877" data-end="932">
<li data-start="877" data-end="932">
<p data-start="879" data-end="932">Properly formatted references for Paper 1 &amp; Paper 2</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start="934" data-end="937">
<p data-start="939" data-end="1139">If you want, I can <strong data-start="958" data-end="1001">now create the full Word seminar report</strong> with all these subheadings, including abstract, literature survey, comparative table, conclusion, and references, ready for submission.</p>
