essage-id="8f034151-75ab-403b-ac97-8f7cd610bd86" dir="auto" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-mini"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="249">Sure Merin! Here’s a <strong data-start="21" data-end="62">detailed Comparative Analysis section</strong> for your seminar paper based on <strong data-start="95" data-end="118">Paper 1 and Paper 2</strong>. I’ve included algorithms, input parameters, application areas, strengths, limitations, and a <strong data-start="213" data-end="246">side-by-side comparison table</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="251" data-end="254">
<h3 data-start="256" data-end="289"><strong data-start="260" data-end="287">3. Comparative Analysis</strong></h3>
<h4 data-start="291" data-end="321"><strong data-start="296" data-end="319">3.1 Algorithms Used</strong></h4>
<ul data-start="322" data-end="898">
<li data-start="322" data-end="619">
<p data-start="324" data-end="619"><strong data-start="324" data-end="336">Paper 1:</strong> Focuses on traditional and foundational AI algorithms in cybersecurity, such as <strong data-start="417" data-end="442">machine learning (ML)</strong> for anomaly detection, <strong data-start="466" data-end="496">signature-based techniques</strong>, and basic predictive analytics. Emphasis is on how these algorithms improve detection accuracy and reduce human errors.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="620" data-end="898">
<p data-start="622" data-end="898"><strong data-start="622" data-end="634">Paper 2:</strong> Highlights <strong data-start="646" data-end="672">advanced AI algorithms</strong> including <strong data-start="683" data-end="700">deep learning</strong>, <strong data-start="702" data-end="739">natural language processing (NLP)</strong>, <strong data-start="741" data-end="772">predictive analytics models</strong>, and <strong data-start="778" data-end="811">automated threat intelligence</strong> systems. These are applied in real-time monitoring and decision-making environments.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="900" data-end="903">
<h4 data-start="905" data-end="947"><strong data-start="910" data-end="945">3.2 Input Parameters / Datasets</strong></h4>
<ul data-start="948" data-end="1332">
<li data-start="948" data-end="1131">
<p data-start="950" data-end="1131"><strong data-start="950" data-end="962">Paper 1:</strong> Uses malware signatures, network traffic logs, user behavior patterns, and vulnerability databases. Focus is mostly on structured datasets and historical attack data.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1132" data-end="1332">
<p data-start="1134" data-end="1332"><strong data-start="1134" data-end="1146">Paper 2:</strong> Incorporates diverse and large datasets, including threat feeds, IoT and cloud data, logs from multiple domains (finance, healthcare, retail), and unstructured data analyzed with NLP.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1334" data-end="1337">
<h4 data-start="1339" data-end="1381"><strong data-start="1344" data-end="1379">3.3 Application Areas / Domains</strong></h4>
<ul data-start="1382" data-end="1781">
<li data-start="1382" data-end="1565">
<p data-start="1384" data-end="1565"><strong data-start="1384" data-end="1396">Paper 1:</strong> General cybersecurity applications across networks, data centers, and enterprise IT systems. Mainly focuses on theoretical and broad-scale cybersecurity improvements.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1566" data-end="1781">
<p data-start="1568" data-end="1781"><strong data-start="1568" data-end="1580">Paper 2:</strong> Specific domain implementations such as <strong data-start="1621" data-end="1642">financial systems</strong>, <strong data-start="1644" data-end="1661">healthcare IT</strong>, <strong data-start="1663" data-end="1681">retail systems</strong>, <strong data-start="1683" data-end="1701">cloud security</strong>, and <strong data-start="1707" data-end="1737">industrial control systems</strong>. Emphasis on practical, real-world usage.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1783" data-end="1786">
<h4 data-start="1788" data-end="1828"><strong data-start="1793" data-end="1826">3.4 Strengths and Limitations</strong></h4>
<div class="TyagGW_tableContainer"><div tabindex="-1" class="group TyagGW_tableWrapper flex w-fit flex-col-reverse"><table data-start="1829" data-end="2531" class="w-fit min-w-(--thread-content-width)"><thead data-start="1829" data-end="1860"><tr data-start="1829" data-end="1860"><th data-start="1829" data-end="1839" data-col-size="sm">Feature</th><th data-start="1839" data-end="1849" data-col-size="lg">Paper 1</th><th data-start="1849" data-end="1860" data-col-size="lg">Paper 2</th></tr></thead><tbody data-start="1893" data-end="2531"><tr data-start="1893" data-end="2146"><td data-start="1893" data-end="1909" data-col-size="sm"><strong data-start="1895" data-end="1908">Strengths</strong></td><td data-start="1909" data-end="2028" data-col-size="lg">Provides clear understanding of AI fundamentals in cybersecurity; highlights limitations and ethical considerations.</td><td data-start="2028" data-end="2146" data-col-size="lg">Covers recent AI advancements; demonstrates practical applications in multiple domains; real-time threat handling.</td></tr><tr data-start="2147" data-end="2336"><td data-start="2147" data-end="2165" data-col-size="sm"><strong data-start="2149" data-end="2164">Limitations</strong></td><td data-start="2165" data-end="2247" data-col-size="lg">Focuses more on theory than implementation; limited discussion of modern tools.</td><td data-start="2247" data-end="2336" data-col-size="lg">Complexity may be high for beginners; relies on advanced AI tools and large datasets.</td></tr><tr data-start="2337" data-end="2531"><td data-start="2337" data-end="2356" data-col-size="sm"><strong data-start="2339" data-end="2355">Future Scope</strong></td><td data-start="2356" data-end="2426" data-col-size="lg">Improve accuracy, reduce false positives, address ethical concerns.</td><td data-start="2426" data-end="2531" data-col-size="lg">Integration with IoT, blockchain, quantum computing; enhanced automation and predictive capabilities.</td></tr></tbody></table><div cla