 w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-mini"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="219">Sure Merin! Here’s a <strong data-start="21" data-end="42">comparative table</strong> you can include in your seminar paper for <strong data-start="85" data-end="108">Paper 1 and Paper 2</strong>. It summarizes <strong data-start="124" data-end="203">algorithms, input datasets, application domains, strengths, and limitations</strong> side by side:</p>
<hr data-start="221" data-end="224">
<h3 data-start="226" data-end="254"><strong data-start="230" data-end="254">7. Comparative Table</strong></h3>
<div class="TyagGW_tableContainer"><div tabindex="-1" class="group TyagGW_tableWrapper flex w-fit flex-col-reverse"><table data-start="256" data-end="1718" class="w-fit min-w-(--thread-content-width)"><thead data-start="256" data-end="354"><tr data-start="256" data-end="354"><th data-start="256" data-end="275" data-col-size="sm">Feature / Aspect</th><th data-start="275" data-end="313" data-col-size="md">Paper 1: Impact &amp; Limitations of AI</th><th data-start="313" data-end="354" data-col-size="lg">Paper 2: Recent Advances &amp; Uses of AI</th></tr></thead><tbody data-start="452" data-end="1718"><tr data-start="452" data-end="677"><td data-start="452" data-end="474" data-col-size="sm"><strong data-start="454" data-end="473">Algorithms Used</strong></td><td data-col-size="md" data-start="474" data-end="572">Machine Learning (ML), Signature-based detection, Anomaly detection, Basic predictive analytics</td><td data-col-size="lg" data-start="572" data-end="677">Deep Learning, NLP, Advanced ML models, Automated threat intelligence, Real-time predictive analytics</td></tr><tr data-start="678" data-end="929"><td data-start="678" data-end="712" data-col-size="sm"><strong data-start="680" data-end="711">Input Parameters / Datasets</strong></td><td data-col-size="md" data-start="712" data-end="803">Malware signatures, Network traffic logs, User behavior patterns, Historical attack data</td><td data-col-size="lg" data-start="803" data-end="929">Threat feeds, IoT/Cloud data, Logs from multiple domains (finance, healthcare, retail), Unstructured data analyzed via NLP</td></tr><tr data-start="930" data-end="1132"><td data-start="930" data-end="964" data-col-size="sm"><strong data-start="932" data-end="963">Application Areas / Domains</strong></td><td data-col-size="md" data-start="964" data-end="1027">General cybersecurity: networks, enterprise IT, data centers</td><td data-col-size="lg" data-start="1027" data-end="1132">Domain-specific applications: finance, healthcare, retail, industrial control systems, cloud security</td></tr><tr data-start="1133" data-end="1335"><td data-start="1133" data-end="1149" data-col-size="sm"><strong data-start="1135" data-end="1148">Strengths</strong></td><td data-col-size="md" data-start="1149" data-end="1234">Provides foundational knowledge; highlights AI’s impact and ethical considerations</td><td data-col-size="lg" data-start="1234" data-end="1335">Shows recent AI advancements; real-world implementations; real-time threat detection and response</td></tr><tr data-start="1336" data-end="1525"><td data-start="1336" data-end="1367" data-col-size="sm"><strong data-start="1338" data-end="1366">Limitations / Challenges</strong></td><td data-col-size="md" data-start="1367" data-end="1432">Focuses more on theory; limited modern implementation examples</td><td data-col-size="lg" data-start="1432" data-end="1525">High complexity; relies on advanced tools and large datasets; may require expert handling</td></tr><tr data-start="1526" data-end="1718"><td data-start="1526" data-end="1545" data-col-size="sm"><strong data-start="1528" data-end="1544">Future Scope</strong></td><td data-col-size="md" data-start="1545" data-end="1614">Improve accuracy, reduce false positives, address ethical concerns</td><td data-col-size="lg" data-start="1614" data-end="1718">Integration with IoT, blockchain, quantum computing; enhanced automation and predictive capabilities</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="sticky h-0 select-none end-(--thread-content-margin) self-end"><div class="absolute end-0 flex items-end" style="height: 32.7969px;"><span class="" data-state="closed"><button aria-label="Copy table" class="hover:bg-token-bg-tertiary text-token-text-secondary my-1 rounded-sm p-1 transition-opacity group-[:not(:hover):not(:focus-within)]:pointer-events-none group-[:not(:hover):not(:focus-within)]:opacity-0"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="icon"><path d="M